            <h2 style="font-size: 1.875rem; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--primary-color);">General Jewelry Care</h2>
            
            <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Fine jewelry is designed to last a lifetime, but proper care is essential to maintain its beauty and integrity. Here are some general guidelines for caring for all types of jewelry:</p>
            
            <ul style="list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Store your jewelry pieces separately to prevent scratching. Consider using a jewelry box with separate compartments or individual pouches.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Remove jewelry before swimming, bathing, or engaging in physical activities. Chlorine, salt water, and perspiration can damage metals and gemstones.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Apply perfume, hairspray, and other cosmetics before putting on your jewelry. Chemicals in these products can cause damage over time.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Clean your jewelry regularly using appropriate methods for each type of piece (see specific care instructions below).</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Have your jewelry professionally inspected and cleaned at least once a year to ensure settings are secure and to maintain its appearance.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
