            <div style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
                <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Gold Jewelry</h3>
                <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Gold jewelry can be cleaned at home using a simple solution of mild dish soap and warm water:</p>
                
                <ol style="list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Mix a few drops of mild dish soap with warm (not hot) water in a small bowl.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Soak the gold jewelry for 10-15 minutes.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Gently brush with a soft-bristled toothbrush, focusing on areas where dirt might accumulate.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Rinse thoroughly with clean water.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Pat dry with a soft, lint-free cloth.</li>
                </ol>
                
                <p style="line-height: 1.6;">Avoid using harsh chemicals or abrasive materials that can scratch the gold's surface. For white gold that has a rhodium plating, be aware that the plating may wear off over time and require re-plating to maintain its bright white appearance.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
                <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Silver Jewelry</h3>
                <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Sterling silver naturally tarnishes over time when exposed to air. To clean tarnished silver:</p>
                
                <ol style="list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Use a silver polishing cloth specifically designed for jewelry.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">For more tarnished pieces, apply a small amount of silver polish with a soft cloth.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Rinse thoroughly and dry completely.</li>
                </ol>
                
                <p style="line-height: 1.6;">To prevent tarnish, store silver jewelry in an airtight container or anti-tarnish bag when not in use. Avoid exposing silver to chlorinated water, sulfur-containing substances, and rubber, which can accelerate tarnishing.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
                <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Diamond Jewelry</h3>
                <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Diamonds are durable but can still collect oils and dirt that diminish their sparkle. To clean diamond jewelry:</p>
                
                <ol style="list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Soak in a solution of warm water and mild dish soap for 20-30 minutes.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Gently brush with a soft toothbrush, especially around the setting and underneath the diamond.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Rinse thoroughly under warm running water (use a strainer in the sink to prevent loss).</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Pat dry with a lint-free cloth.</li>
                </ol>
                
                <p style="line-height: 1.6;">While diamonds are the hardest natural substance, they can still chip if struck at the right angle. Avoid wearing diamond jewelry during rough activities, and have the settings checked regularly to ensure the stones are secure.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
                <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Gemstone Jewelry</h3>
                <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Different gemstones require different care, as some are more delicate than others:</p>
                
                <ul style="list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Sapphires and Rubies:</strong> These are quite durable and can be cleaned similarly to diamonds.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Emeralds:</strong> More fragile and often treated with oils. Clean gently with a soft brush and mild soap. Avoid ultrasonic cleaners.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Pearls:</strong> Extremely delicate. Wipe with a soft, damp cloth after wearing. Never soak pearls or use ultrasonic cleaners. Store separately as they can be scratched easily.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Opals:</strong> Sensitive to temperature changes and drying out. Clean with a damp cloth only and avoid chemical cleaners.</li>
                </ul>
                
                <p style="line-height: 1.6;">When in doubt about how to clean a particular gemstone, consult with a professional jeweler.</p>
